Recommended Setup
Host Machine (Windows)

Install:

Oracle VirtualBox

or
VMware Workstation Player
VM Requirements

Minimum:

8 GB RAM
4 CPU cores
80 GB disk

Recommended:

16 GB RAM
6+ CPU cores
100 GB disk
Step 1 — Download Ubuntu Server

Download Ubuntu 22.04 LTS:

Ubuntu Server ISO

Step 2 — Create Ubuntu VM

Recommended VM settings:

Setting	Value
RAM	8–16 GB
CPU	4
Disk	80 GB
Network	Bridged Adapter

Install Ubuntu normally.

Step 3 — Login and Update Ubuntu
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Step 4 — Install Git
sudo apt install git -y
Step 5 — Create stack User
sudo useradd -s /bin/bash -d /opt/stack -m stack

Set password:

sudo passwd stack

Give sudo access:

echo "stack ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL" | sudo tee /etc/sudoers.d/stack

Switch user:

su - stack
Step 6 — Download DevStack
git clone https://opendev.org/openstack/devstack

Go to directory:

cd devstack
Step 7 — Create local.conf
nano local.conf

Paste this:

[[local|localrc]]

ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin
DATABASE_PASSWORD=admin
RABBIT_PASSWORD=admin
SERVICE_PASSWORD=admin

HOST_IP=127.0.0.1

Save:

CTRL + O
Enter
CTRL + X
Step 8 — Install OpenStack

Run:

./stack.sh

This takes 20–45 minutes.

Step 9 — Access OpenStack Dashboard

After installation, open browser:

http://YOUR_VM_IP/dashboard

Username:

admin

Password:

admin
Find VM IP Address

Run:

ip a

Look for something like:

192.168.x.x
Useful OpenStack Commands
Load admin credentials
source openrc admin admin
Check services
openstack service list
Create network
openstack network create private-net
Create VM instance
openstack server list
Optional: Use Packstack (Alternative)

For beginners, DevStack is easier.

Packstack is more production-like but mainly supports:

Red Hat Enterprise Linux
CentOS
